      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since this magic hundred appears here and in FiletimeToTimespecEpoch, it should probably be a constant with a self-documenting name, and even defined in a reasonable way.\n\n  static constexpr uint64_t kNanosecondsPerSecond \u003d static_cast\u003cuint64_t\u003e(1E9);\n  static constexpr uint64_t kNanosecondsPerFiletimeInterval \u003d kNanosecondsPerSecond / kFiletimeIntervalsPerSecond;\n\nNow that I’m thinking along those lines, up in FiletimeToMicroseconds(), we could also have a more self-documenting “kFiletimeIntervalsPerMicrosecond \u003d kFiletimeIntervalsPerSecond / kMicrosecondsPerSecond” instead of the magic ten, obviating the need for the comment.",
